description.narrative: UNICEF enhanced support to child protection service provision by key Government partners such as the MOLSW, LWU and the JJCC through training of their staff on related knowledge and skill sets as well as supply of relevant equipment. These resulted in improved access to health services by CWD; the upgrading of hotline and counselling services at the LWU Center for the Protection of Women and Child Victims of Violence and Trafficking; and the legal services offered to the children in contact with the law through the expansion of community-based legal and social assistance, and a diversion program. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
